        <heading>NEGOTIATIONS - GOV'T. CONCESSIONS</heading>
        <speech by="#3dc88fea-b098-4360-8284-83133daa16fa">
          <from>MR. CHUCK PORTER</from>
          <p>MR. CHUCK PORTER : Mr. Speaker, my question this afternoon is for the Minister of Health and Wellness. Paramedics have been engaged in negotiations for some time. In late February we learned that paramedics voted 98 per cent in favour of rejecting their employer's offer. That was with 95 per cent coming out of the membership. The government and paramedics are reportedly far apart.</p>
